<font face=Arial,Helvetica>
<b>The Selfishness of the Unselfish</b><br><font face=Arial,Helvetica size=1>Posted on  Tuesday, August 01 @ 15:16:15 EDT

</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td bgcolor=ffffff>
<font face=Arial,Helvetica>
<a href=search.php3?query=&topic=11&author=><img src=images/topics/libertyboard.jpg border=0 Alt="Libertyboard.org" align=right hspace=10 vspace=10></a>
<P>Found this little gem called <A href="http://www.fee.org/iol/00/0006/boudreaux.html">The Selfishness of the Unselfish</A> while perusing today's news links over on <A href="http://www.libertysearch.com/">Libertysearch.com</A>.  In the article, Foundation for Economic Education president Donald Boudreaux eloquently turns the tables on those who claim moral superiority over 'greedy capitalists' by virtue of their unselfishness.</P>

<P>Very good stuff.  Anyone have links to other articles that help deflate the rantings of the 'libertarians are uncaring greedy capitalist scum' crowd?</P> 
</td>
</tr>
